column11: HIGH- UP APPROX. 1' FROM LAST FALL

column2: First day since the last reading with sun and calm water.
Sunny- clear sky- last reading till next spring- ice forming in the bay.
Ice off 4-13 5 p.m.  Very slight waves - clear + sunny.
Partly cloudy-stiff south breeze-somewhat rough water.
Calm-few clouds. bench mark of 100' established on stump at western lot line near water at 6209 minnow lake rd.
20 years ago-swim without showering afterward-now we shower!  hot! -calm water-water coated with pollen-some floating weeds and grass.
Partly cloudy-slight breeze-water much dirtier than at ice out.
Partly cloudy-moderate waves-water level down about 6" since ice-out.
Clear sky-moderate waves-swimming and aesthetic enjoyment very impaired-would not swim.
Clear sky-moderate waves.  Lake level down 10" since ice out.
Partly cloudy-calm water.  Much rain this last week.  Water level up 6+".
Very few clouds-slight waves.  Beautiful fall day!
Clear with few clouds- surface plants killed off from frosts- considerable rain with some snow in the last 5 days.
Partly cloudy- windy- ice out 4/28. coldest winter in 19 years.  Bottom sample- no depth reported- assumed 50'.  Water level: up approx. 1'
Pollen + floating weeds. no clouds-hot! hot! hot! slight breeze. very little rain.
Silt and muck continues to build up in north bay to less than 1' from surface- sand bottom is 16-18' deep.
Surprise- depth better this time-lake looks better than last 2 years.
Clear sky- slight breeze.  Our bay is covered with lily pads.
Change from last reading of 11'. May be due to heavy rain and high winds 2 nights before.
Partly cloudy-north breeze. first frosts on the 11th (26 degrees) + 12th (22 degrees) .
Partly cloudy- breezy- fall has arrived in all its colorful splendor!
Ice off 4/20/97- clear sky- very little breeze.
Much pollen on surface last 2 weeks.  Swimming okay but must shower after swim.  Clear sky- hot- little breeze.

Depth back up to 13 feet- probably due to high water and less motor activity to chop up weed beds and high winds and heavy waves have carried most weeds- sod chunks- loose boards- etc. into our N bay.
Weed beds all under water.  Abundant lily pads in north bay.  Swimming okay- but shower after.  Clear sky- slight breeze.
Ice off 3/31. mallards are back.  Dry conditions.
Clear light waves.  2 geese followed by 5 goslings near my bog frontage.
Partly cloudy calm. weeds and pads clogging north bay.
Partly cloudy light breeze.  Weed beds show above low water.  Mother duck and 5 young near deep hole 7/18.
Overcast lake level lowest in 24 years.

Clear sky - north wind causes water to appear dirty over deep hole. note: 7/26/99: raked 4 1/2 barrels of weeds (amer milfoil) from neighbor's beach- then using his beach to monitor- as my access is clogged with lily pads- floating bogs and weeds!
Clear sky - hot - moderate breeze - motors of large boats tearing up weedbeds- causing excess of weeds in north bay.
Clear sky - warm - calm water - weed beds spreading.
Mostly clear sky - slight breeze - light waves.
Colder than usual for early oct. - windy - partly cloudy.
Early ice out 3/24/2000. lake level very low
Clear sky- sunny. 4 canada geese- 2 mallards and 27 turtles sunning on the bogs.
Clear sky- slight breeze. mallard with 8 young in the bay. much water ski and jet ski activity.
Partly cloudy- slight breeze. My granddaughter wouldn't swim in the lake after July 4th- she said it was yucky and I agree.
Delayed one day for satellite.  Water too rough 9/29.
clear sky calm water dirty water
Cloudy- lots of rain (3" in 2 days).
partly clody- warm with slight sw breeze
cloudy day about 68 with slight breeze out of the SW--   again some areas on lake had a lot of those - what I call water spiders- zippin around.  Two loons on the lake and hurin.
sunny + clear- slight south breze.  2 Loons on lake
heavy overcast- about 50 degrees- slight wind from the east.
was a rainy weekend- overcast day-calm-72 degees was a rainy weekend- overcast day-calm-72 degrees-spotty areas of veg. showing  just below water surface probably because water surface was flat
clear sky--windy from the sw   more than usual weed groth visable on surface
windy ---partly cloudy---75 degrees windy ---partly cloudy---75 degrees
clear sky 78 degrees- slight SW breeze-  water looks real clean and clear
overcast-  65degrees- slight sw breeze overcast-  65degrees- slight sw breeze- pollen on surface
73 degrees- slight overcast- sw wind @5mph- little chop on water
85 degreese- partly cloudy- slight sw breeze
82 degrees- few clouds- slight SE breeze -  water appeared to have some pollen  on surface probably due to stormy weather previous days.
some clouds- 82 degrees- slight SW wind
mostly sunny  78 degrees slight breeze sw
46 degrees- overcast and calm-pollen on surface and suspended deep intp water column and some sludge like pollen on shoreline.
75 degrees sunny with light clouds- slight NE breeze very little pollen on surface
mostly cloudy-air temp about 82--slight sw breeze  water looked good

mostly sunny- 83 degrees wind from the sw- sediment from weeds distrubed from motors  in uper layers of water- otherwise water looked good- eagle flying  above.   Was a very hot week.  about 1/4 inch of rain day before testing.
mostly sunny- 85 degrees with a slight sw breeze- very little vegitation floating in water from motor boats.
clear and sunny- 70 degrees- SW breeze
clear and sunny- southeast breeze beautiful day- water looked really clear

mostly cloudy - 65 degrees- sw wind about 10mph- 2 loons and a few geese. partly sunny- 68 degrees- 10mphSW wind- water higher than last year at this time- but still lower than  a few years ago.   Saw 2 loons
temp was 84 degrees- partly cludy with sw wind at 10-15mph
Weather was hot during past week.   Day of test tempwas 73 and overcast with nw wind 5-10mph.
mostly sunny---68degrees slight  sw wind--- eagle flying around

column1: Question if temp gauge is working accurate as readings did not very much.

column2: clear sky- 80 degrees with SW ;wind about 8-10mph-----2 loons on the lake and some ducks.   Grandkids helped- Thomas and Jonny.
Did not do Secchi as sky was heavily overcast
85 degrees- parley cloudy- 5-10 SW breeze- 2 loons on lake- was a light rain early morning. beautiful day
Partly sunny-75 degrees with south wind 5-10mph
nice day -little overcast about 78 degrees -slight sw wind
75 degrees- partly cloudy slight sw breeze
partly sunny about 80 degrees and slight sw wind
nice day - 78 degrees-  slight southern breeze mostly sunny.   about 2 inches of rain past 24 hours.
65 degrees- calm- blue sky.  Observed 2 adult loons.
Clear- Sunny- Wind from S.W.' Lots of rain + pine pollen.
lake depth 23 Feet- Many boats pulling innertubes.
partly cloudy- much rain (over 4.0")- high winds (lake stirred up)
Data collector's name is actually David Thorsen; system not accepting change
Dave Thorsen is the data collector
High Pollen - cotton wood seeds - partly sunny
Almost Clear Skies Almost clear skies- windy
Very Windy-  Prior days rainy.  Waves (lots)
Partly Sunny - Water had ripples- hard to see.
calm- many clouds- nice day- warm- sediment in water- lots of weekend water traffic.
